    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When the control is configured as continuous (see "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nscontrol/1428952-continuous"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "), the interval between repeating actions automatically adjusts to match the applied pressure. As the user presses harder, actions are sent more rapidly. As the user reduces pressure, actions slow down. As such, the user has direct control over how fast actions are sent. Continuous momentary accelerator segmented controls are intended for continuously advancing through a series of discrete objects, such as photos in an album or pages in a book."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When configured as noncontinuous, actions are sent whenever a change in pressure occurs. Noncontinuous momentary accelerator segmented controls are intended for adjusting the speed of navigation, such as playback speed in a media player, based on pressure. Once the control is released, a final action is sent."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When the user force clicks a segment in the control, "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nssegmentedcontrol/1534490-selectedsegment"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " value is the index of the active segment, and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nssegmentedcontrol/1529727-doublevalueforselectedsegment"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is a measurement of pressure between "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "1.0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and approaching "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "2.0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". When the user releases pressure, the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nssegmentedcontrol/1534490-selectedsegment"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " value is "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "-1"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nssegmentedcontrol/1529727-doublevalueforselectedsegment"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "0.0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "On a system that doesn’t support pressure sensitivity, a momentary accelerator segmented control behaves like a control of type "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nssegmentswitchtracking/nssegmentswitchtrackingmomentary"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
